cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.ME, cs.ET, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with soft robotic actuators and locomotion control experiments. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper proposes a constraint-based dynamics model for the soft actuator and accounts for actuator latency and damping. 
- cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering) is another possible category as the paper deals with the physical modeling of soft robotic actuators. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is a possible category as soft robotics is a relatively new and emerging field. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also possible as the paper leverages the parallel computation power of GPUs for real-time performance.
